job_history.work_description: Diligently maintained living environment for three individuals and two pets all while completing Bachelors of Science through distance learning.

Essential member of the Army communications maintenance team and is primarily responsible for performing field and sustainment level maintenance on avionic navigation flight control systems, stabilization systems and equipment.
Coordinated and scheduled training visits, briefings, appointments, correspondences and travel arrangements for the 1st Infantry Division Deputy Commanding General/Senior Commander.
Supervised, trained and led up to 5 soldiers on a daily basis. Responsible for creating and maintaining the Brigades operation orders, detailing and delegating tasks to subordinate units.

Coordinated and scheduled training visits, briefings, appointments, correspondences and travel arrangements. Executed over 15 boards and 27 award ceremonies recognizing Soldiers and Civilians who contribute to esprit de corps and superior performance of duty.
Served as the administrative assistant for brigade command group. Instructor for brigade junior leader course, mentoring and developing 54 students across a three month period.
Personally responsible for developing and utilizing a company database to efficiently maintaining personnel records for 320 personnel and family readiness rosters.

Maintains adequate stock of resale items. Operated a computer system that calculates and marks prices Operated an electronic checkout system, makes change, and verifies change fund and amount of currency received during an assigned shift.
